# Installation Guidelines

## Prerequisites

- Python 3.x
- pip (Python package manager)

## Steps

1. Ensure you have Python and pip installed on your system.
2. Clone this repository: `git clone https://github.com/yourusername/ProteinViz2PDF.git`
3. Navigate into the project directory: `cd ProteinViz2PDF`
4. Install the required Python packages:
    ```
    pip install -r requirements.txt
    ```

That's it! You're now set up and ready to convert PDB files into PDF visualizations.
